discourse_list.title: StarkNet Token Launch & Request for Support

content.content: As many are aware, StarkNet is launching its token soon Part 1: StarkNet Sovereignty: A Decentralization Proposal | by StarkWare | StarkWare | Jul, 2022 | Medium Congratulations but noted that there’s a sizable portion for grants and collaboration. This post is made to check whether StarkNet team will be interested in providing such grants or rewards to the Maker protocol. The Maker protocol has allocated $millions into collaborating with StarkNet and believe it’s a nice gesture from StarkNet to commit to such.
@pyramidmaker If there is already such support from StarkNet side, please share with the community

Thank you @Doo_StableLab for bringing this up. The foundation distributing the token is not fully setup yet, it will happen within the next 6 months. I will investigate and revert back. Note that the deal with Starkware is that Starkware is covering 50% of all development costs, Maker is paying the other 50%.
pyramidmaker:  months. I will investigate and revert back.   Thank you

pyramidmaker:  Note that the deal with Starkware is that Starkware is covering 50% of all development costs, Maker is paying the other 50%.   So doesn’t this mean that Maker should get like 50% of the token distribution.
Good heuristic  I will connect with the soon-to-be-launched foundation and update

Even if it is beneficial to Maker, the community is negatively impacted on cryptotwitter by the 50% direct or indirect distribution to Devs, Investors and others. Do you think that this is not frowned upon by the various communities in the ecosystem?
